CBF Documenattion

Packages 
Package Description
app1.hartford
Classes to run component based test cases, in component library
cbf.component  
cbf.engine
Classes to run component based test cases, to track the runtime status of execution, and to encapsulate runtime exception handling, test failures and recovery.
cbf.harness
Classes necessary to initialize the framework configurations.
cbf.model
Provides all the core interfaces related to framework.
cbf.utils
Provides generic utilities to be used across the framework
cbfx.cli
This package contains Main methods for both parallel and sequential execution along with Helper class which contains supporting methods for run arguments
cbfx.factory.data
Provides classes necessary to fetch the component data from different data sources like database, excel etc
cbfx.factory.report
Manages different types of reporting like excel, html, alm, email etc.
cbfx.factory.test
Classes to manage testsets and testcases from different sources ALM,Designer, Json, Excel, Xml and to take care of deserializing test case after resolving the test case and data mapping for execution.
cbfx.testng
Provides classes for parallel/cross browser execution.
cbfx.ui.appium
Provides Classes necessary to execute tests in mobile
cbfx.ui.browser
Manages multiple browsers along with their required properties
cbfx.ui.eggplant
Provides the classes to execute the GUI tests
cbfx.ui.objectmap
Contains classes for reading ObjectMap (UI Element identifiers) from Excel or Xml file.
cbfx.ui.seetest
Provides the classes to run the same test on different mobile devices and operating systems that allows test portability
cbfx.ui.selenium
Provides Wrapper supporting classes for handling selenium related functionalities.
cbfx.ui.sikuli
Provides an object-oriented abstraction on top of Sikuli to assist with interacting GUI elements
cbfx.ui.web
Provides necessary classes that creating new browser session for execution.
cbfx.utils
Provides utilities which contains cbfx supporting functions and classes
